<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">FADE AND SHADOW STEP</b></font> - <small>Yendiin, Xegony</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    What I am about to say may seem trival to some but this tactic has saved my life.  I believe these are two of the most effective spells in the spell book as for survival (fade and shadow step). <P>

When doing battle it is well known we root and burn.  If the MOB breaks root I will not attempt a second due to the mana waste. I will then attempt to get in the shock spells for they are much faster to cast, timing the strike of the mob by watching the red text, when hit, cast. <P> 

If lucky you can burn before you fall, if the mob is getting the better end due to random or double strike, then fade and cast shock for there is no line of site required. Keep an eye on the mana and do not become over zealous in your kill if the going gets tough shadow step (has further distance) and gate (I usually bind outside of the zone).<P>

 Shadow step is preferred due to the distance over fade. i.e. I was attacked (while medding)by a Griffon in the West Commons and hit shadow step and then zoned with min. damage. Everyone was amazed when I returned and questioned -- how did you manage that? -- My reply was "I'm a Wizard" hahaha. (I was shocked myself that I pulled it off -- shhhhhh!)<P>

Lastly, these spells are random so beware you may tele. three feet from where you where standing :( -- if so hit again until you can gate.  And please do not use near water such as NRO, you could find yourself in deep waters and being attacked by your trgt. which swim pretty fast.. :) Be aware of your surroundings i.e. orc camps and such.<P>

Shadow Step consumes 10 mana.(very fast cast time)<br>
Fade        consumes 10 mana.(very fast cast time)<br>
Gate        consumes 70 mana.(slow cast time)<br>
Root consumes 40 mana (avg. cast time)<p>

(Find a safe place and Fade all over the place to max this skill at every lvl.)<p>

I hope this helps, I tend to get long winded and for that I apologize.. :)<p>

All the best and dont give up..<p>

Yendiin<br>
High Elf


 

		
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
